beauty gone, my glory forgotten.  I couldn't dance at all anymore.  They drug me around and threw me aside.  I sensed my end was near.  My life cut short from my brothers.<br>
<br>
I lay there on the ground, listening to men talk, laughing about what would become of me, though I didn't understand.  Then one day they came for me and I knew my end had finally come.  I was dragged into such a magnificent structure where men in helmets stood.  And then I saw him.  A man who looked much like me.  Stripped and humiliated, a mere shell of what he must have been like before.  He looked as rough and beaten up as I did and I knew we were meant for each other.  They carried me to the man and placed me on his shoulder, I could hear the cruelty in their voices as they spoke to this poor man who was clearly too tired and beaten to drag me around.<br>
<br>
But drag me he did, out the gates and into the narrow street lined with more people than I had seen in my entire lifetime.  They jeered at the poor man as we went down the street together.  I felt bad, I should carry him.  And finally he fell, my weight was too much for him.  So they put me on someone else's shoulder, a man not beaten or weary who carried me on down the street.<br>
<br>
We came to this hill, and I knew this was the end.  They laid me on the ground and then they laid that poor, beaten man on top of me.  A cross, I heard someone call me, I suppose I was no longer a tree.  And I felt the man's blood pour into me as nails bound us together.  Never had I been so close to another creature in all my life.  We were now united to die together.<br>
<br>
They lifted us up and oh the shame of it all.  For our glory and all been taken away.  And then this poor, beaten man spoke.  He asked His Father to forgive these people.  Oh the love of this man.  It was my honor to die with Him.  And in that moment, I felt my glory restored.  Not just restored, but I felt more beautiful than I had with all my leaves at the peak of my life.  Let those people jeer and laugh, I was the only tree ever united with the one who created me.  And they're nothing compared to Him.<br>
